{"title":"OpenRoboCare: A Multimodal Multi-Task Expert Demonstration Dataset for Robot Caregiving","domain":"ROBOTICS","seeds":[{"problem":"Robot caregiving lacks a large-scale, diverse, expert-collected multimodal dataset that captures real-world ADLs with occlusions, rich physical contact, caregiver attention, and long-horizon task structure.","method":"OpenRoboCare provides 315 expert sessions (19.8 h) from 21 occupational therapists across 15 ADL tasks on two manikins, recorded in five synchronized modalities: RGB-D video, pose tracking (mocap plus an occlusion-robust video-pose pipeline using manual labels to fine-tune YOLOv11 and triangulated 3D keypoints), eye-gaze, natural-language task/action annotations, and a custom whole-body tactile skin (88 resistive sensors, calibrated to force). Data, documentation, and the fine-tuned pose model are released."},{"problem":"Robots lack distilled expert caregiving strategies and quantitative interaction patterns to inform control timing, contact planning, and hardware requirements.","method":"The authors analyze demonstrations to extract OT guiding principles (pre-positioning, anticipation, efficiency) and concrete techniques (e.g., bridge, segmental roll, wheelchair recline, stabilizing key control points). They quantify caregiver gaze look-ahead (~2.02 s), contact distributions across body regions, and force ranges (≈0.1–2 N for gentle tasks vs >20–30 N for demanding repositioning), and translate these into guidelines for policy lookahead and hardware design (e.g., distributed whole-arm compliance and sensing)."},{"problem":"State-of-the-art pose perception and long-horizon activity recognition models generalize poorly to caregiving scenarios with heavy occlusions, multi-body contact, and domain shift.","method":"Using OpenRoboCare as a benchmark, the paper evaluates 2D/3D pose estimation and task recognition: off-the-shelf YOLOv11 yields very low 2D mAP, but fine-tuning on small subsets (1–5 OTs) yields large gains, especially for occlusion-heavy dressing and transfer; 3D baselines (RTMOPose3D, MixSTE, HoT, MHFormer) report notable MPJPEs. VidChapters-7M on long videos shows terminology and segmentation failures (e.g., mislabeling 'Hoyer'), highlighting the dataset’s challenge and headroom for improvement."}]}
